    dc:description "FIGURE 25. Neaxius glyptocercus (von Martens, 1869): A, B—smaller male (cl 17.2 mm) from Sira, Lombok, Indonesia (RMDH. CRUS. D. 56756), A—lateral view; B—dorsal view; C—larger male (cl 19.0 mm) from the same locality (ZRC 2014.0742), lateral view (both specimens with characters of N. acanthus (A. Milne-Edwards 1878 ))." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/254450/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

